WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:03.549
Let's now look at what happens when a Problem Task is assigned to your group.

1
00:00:03.930 --> 00:00:06.550
We're starting this scenario logged in as a Problem Manager.

2
00:00:07.010 --> 00:00:07.769
As you can see,

3
00:00:07.849 --> 00:00:10.310
the Problem is in the Root Cause Analysis state.

4
00:00:10.609 --> 00:00:12.329
And here on the Problem Tasks tab,

5
00:00:12.529 --> 00:00:16.690
we can see that the Problem Manager has created a Root Cause Analysis Task

6
00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:18.770
and assigned it to the relevant support group.

7
00:00:19.129 --> 00:00:22.530
Let's now log in as a member of that assignment group and pick up the task.

8
00:00:22.930 --> 00:00:25.790
Head to the Tasks list and select "Assigned to your group".

9
00:00:26.290 --> 00:00:29.489
Here you'll find any assigned Problem Tasks in your team's queue,

10
00:00:29.889 --> 00:00:31.549
alongside other task types,

11
00:00:31.850 --> 00:00:34.169
like Incidents or Service Catalog Tasks.

12
00:00:36.279 --> 00:00:40.419
Review the task details in the Short Description and Description fields.

13
00:00:41.340 --> 00:00:42.500
To take ownership of the task,

14
00:00:42.549 --> 00:00:44.009
click "Assign to me".

15
00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:48.020
This populates your name in the Assigned To field.

16
00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:50.840
When you're ready to begin,

17
00:00:51.139 --> 00:00:52.430
click "Start work",

18
00:00:52.619 --> 00:00:54.459
to move the task to Work in Progress.

19
00:00:55.849 --> 00:00:57.979
You can easily navigate to the parent problem record

20
00:00:57.979 --> 00:01:00.119
by clicking the info button on the Problem field.

21
00:01:01.720 --> 00:01:03.159
Then choosing "Open Record".

22
00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:06.290
The record opens in a new tab within the workspace.

23
00:01:07.190 --> 00:01:07.750
From here,

24
00:01:07.949 --> 00:01:10.089
you can view the full details of the Problem,

25
00:01:10.389 --> 00:01:12.470
as well as the previous activity on the record.

26
00:01:17.089 --> 00:01:20.769
You can also check the Related Records tab to see any related Incidents,

27
00:01:21.059 --> 00:01:24.230
and the Affected Configuration Items and Service Offerings

28
00:01:24.559 --> 00:01:27.129
to get a better understanding of the issue you're investigating.

29
00:01:28.889 --> 00:01:30.419
Let's head back to the Problem Task.

30
00:01:31.930 --> 00:01:34.099
As you work the Root Cause Analysis task,

31
00:01:34.339 --> 00:01:38.019
you can record your findings in the Analysis Information section of the form.

32
00:01:39.319 --> 00:01:42.900
Select the Cause Code that best reflects what you've identified so far.

33
00:01:43.190 --> 00:01:44.739
This doesn't need to be perfect.

34
00:01:44.919 --> 00:01:47.239
It should simply represent the most likely cause

35
00:01:47.239 --> 00:01:49.150
based on the evidence available at this point.

36
00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:50.669
In the Cause Notes field,

37
00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.540
document your observations in clear factual detail.

38
00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:55.389
Focus on what you reviewed,

39
00:01:55.559 --> 00:01:56.540
what you observed,

40
00:01:56.750 --> 00:01:59.139
and any patterns or conditions that stood out.

41
00:01:59.440 --> 00:02:01.360
This helps the Problem Manager understand your

42
00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:03.440
findings without needing to retrace your steps.

43
00:02:05.029 --> 00:02:06.680
In the Proposed Fix Notes field,

44
00:02:06.750 --> 00:02:08.809
capture any suggested next steps.

45
00:02:09.070 --> 00:02:10.710
This might be a potential fix,

46
00:02:11.029 --> 00:02:12.889
a recommendation for further investigation,

47
00:02:13.789 --> 00:02:16.509
or an idea that should be evaluated through Change.

48
00:02:16.789 --> 00:02:18.589
You're not committing to a solution here -- 

49
00:02:19.029 --> 00:02:21.509
you're sharing insight to support the next decision.

50
00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:28.440
If you identify a new or improved workaround while investigating,

51
00:02:28.919 --> 00:02:31.419
you can document it in the Workaround field.

52
00:02:31.759 --> 00:02:34.419
This is especially helpful if Incidents are still occurring

53
00:02:34.720 --> 00:02:36.839
or are waiting on the Problem for guidance.

54
00:02:37.779 --> 00:02:38.970
Once you've entered your notes,

55
00:02:39.179 --> 00:02:41.339
click "Complete" to close the task.

56
00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:42.690
In the modal window,

57
00:02:42.740 --> 00:02:44.820
you can review and finalize your notes,

58
00:02:45.059 --> 00:02:45.809
if needed,

59
00:02:46.339 --> 00:02:49.699
before clicking "Submit" to save your changes and mark the task Complete.
